  "metadata": {
    "what_it_measures": "Producer Price Index for Final Demand. BLS. Monthly, day before or after CPI. Measures wholesale/input inflation. Final demand goods most relevant.\n",
    "why_it_matters": "Pipeline pressure on margins. PPI leads CPI by ~3-6 months. Rising PPI compresses margins before CPI catches up. Relevant for industrials/semis.\n",
    "scoring_rule": "YoY change vs historical average. Phase 3."
